PerfectDisk is a defragmentation software product for Windows developed by Raxco.
During the 1980s, a software package titled "Disk-Optimizer" was marketed as part of the collective name "RAXCO Rabbit Software." PerfectDisk was released in 1990 for the VMS operating system, version for Windows NT followed later in 1997. PerfectDisk contains sheduler supporting also client PCs in the network. The application keeps track of file usage to lessen defragmentation time and offers two modes of basic defragging - quick and SmartPlacement.
